{"title":"Wolf Tooth B-Rad Everywhere Base adds two or three bolt mounts anywhere on your bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/08/wolf-tooth-b-rad-everywhere-base-adds-two-or-three-bolt-mounts-anywhere-on-your-bike/","date":1625777242000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Want to carry more stuff on your bike but don’t have any more mounts? Wolf Tooth is once again coming to the rescue. Expanding on the excellent B-RAD Strap Base, the new B-RAD Everywhere Bases add the ability to run three bolt accessories for increased cargo capabilities.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x322/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth B-RAD Everywhere base for three bolt accessories. \" width=\"590\" height=\"393\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x322/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" ezoid=\"0.38450852481429343\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163128/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-nalgene-bottle-detail-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth B-RAD Everywhere base three bolt\" width=\"590\" height=\"339\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt.jpg 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-297x171.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-120x69.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt.jpg 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-297x171.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163135/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-three-bolt-120x69.jpg 120w\"></a></p><p>It may not look like much, but the silicone-backed hook-and-loop straps are surprisingly secure when cinched tight to your frame. The included EVA foam pads keep the aluminum bracket from touching your frame too, so if you decide to remove it in the future, there’s no damage to the finish.</p><p>The new Everywhere Base 3 adds a three bolt adapter bracket to match up with popular accessories that use a ‘three pack’ mounting system. The kit includes shorter T25 Torx hardware to mount the accessories to the bracket, so the bolt doesn’t protrude into the frame.</p><p>The Everywhere Base 3 is priced at $29.95.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle.jpg\" alt=\"adding a bottle cage to a bike without mounts\" width=\"590\" height=\"393\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle.jpg 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle-120x80.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle.jpg 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163139/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-bottle-120x80.jpg 120w\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth B-RAD Everywhere base two bolt\" width=\"590\" height=\"339\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt.jpg 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-297x171.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-120x69.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt.jpg 590w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-297x171.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08163146/Wolf-Tooth-Components-BRAD-everywhere-strap-base-two-bolt-120x69.jpg 120w\"></a></p><p>Wolf Tooth will also offer the Everywhere 2 which is the same concept, just with two bolts instead of three. This replaces the original B-Rad Strap base, which I’ve <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/11/06/what-to-pack-the-best-gear-for-self-supported-credit-card-touring-on-the-road/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">used with complete success</a> to add a top tube accessory bag to a frame that lacked mounts. Initially, I didn’t expect the Strap Base to be able to hold the bag in place without moving due to the amount of leverage on it, but Wolf Tooth proved me wrong with a rock solid mount that wouldn’t budge.</p><p>The Everywhere 2 is priced at $24.95. Both are available now.</p><h2>Tech Specs</h2><p><strong>Length: </strong>Everywhere Base 2 (10cm), Everywhere Base 3 (14 cm)<br><strong>Weight:&nbsp;</strong>Everywhere Base 2 + hardware (38g), Everywhere Base 3 + hardware (50g)<br><strong>Strap Length:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;30cm (12″) can be trimmed to length as needed<br><strong>Material:</strong>&nbsp; 6061-T6 aluminum brackets&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>|</strong>&nbsp; EVA foam pads<strong><br>Tools Needed:&nbsp;</strong>T25 Torx<br><strong>Made in the&nbsp;USA</strong></p><p><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/products/b-rad-everywhere-base?goal=0_a9cee98036-78bfd9b32a-316393249&amp;mc_cid=78bfd9b32a&amp;mc_eid=f3f2eae96a\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>wolftoothcomponents.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"87bf5aa241fd570acd6346010e0ba3be7e8a5d0d61f19a9a610c6c9e4cc91f3a","category":"Cycling"}